rComments: One of the only good science profs at uOttawa. He cares for your success and is always down to improve his class. His tests are not only fact-based, but require a bit of thinking skills and are open book !! I love him and always recommend him to my peers.

GBD is an S-Tier prof! Lectures are super interesting and gives concrete example that will help you understand the theory and are similar to the questions on the exam. For this class, would recommend taking notes actively and after each lectures, create questions on Anki or other apps. Liked him so much that I took his BIO 3515 next semester

GBD is an all around amazing professor who brings a lot of passion about ecology to his class. Our exams were in person but they were open book, I heavily recommend making mind maps to understand all the concepts discussed in class. He's very specific about answers on exams so be aware. His powerpoints don't have much text so take lots of notes.

Bon professeur. Il est disponible pour répondre à nos questions et veut que les étudiants comprennent la matière. Il incorpore ses propres recherches et montre des exemples concrets à des concepts. Il faut être vrm attentif en classe pour comprendre. Il donne pas de textbook ou d'aide pour étudier. Exam livre ouvert donc ça aide. Il y a des maths.
Literally a gem, I love this man. His testing is kinda out of nowhere but just try to make connections in class and you'll get it
Pretty straight forward, interesting lectures, encouraging.
Great class that was focused on understanding the concepts rather than memorization.

The class itself is interesting, but he over complicates it when teaching. Also, the exams do not represent the material learned in class (very abstract) and questions on subjects that he barely taught and didn't seem important. The corrector mentioned things not learned in class on my exam correction. Very harsh grader and difficult homework's.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Graded by few things', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Is quick to judge and not very approachable. Has a better-than-thou attitude with students that seek more clarity or further explanation on his comments or grading. Not a prof you'll remember 30 years from now when you think back on the good old days and the people that shaped your future.

He is a little arrogant and have no time to waste to help students. Not very approachable, and makes complicated explanation, when thee concept could be explained more simply. Don't ask him any question out of the blue, make sure to REALLY know your stuff. This class is not an a bird class, he expect more than understanding basics.
Very interesting, generous and knowledgeable professor.

You need to make sure to REALLY understand the concept (not just in a general way) and his exams imply applying them in detail... I suggest practicing... ps. his name is gabriel bloUin-demers..lol!  I really like his enthousiasm and he has really cool simple slides... best to show up for class every day this way you can do without the manual
